In this article, Vice President Mike Pence discusses the recent protests in Iran and criticizes the Obama administration for not supporting the Iranian people during the Green Revolution in 2009. Pence praises President Trump for offering unwavering support to the Iranian people and condemns the Iranian regime for its repression and support of terrorism. He also calls on other nations to condemn Iran's actions and defend the Iranian people's right to freedom. Pence emphasizes the United States' commitment to supporting the protesters and ensuring peace and security in the world.